.TH phoenixdkim2-undo 8 "PhoenixDKIM"
.SH NAME
.B phoenixdkim2-undo
\- reconstruct an earlier DKIM2 Message-Instance (test tool)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B phoenixdkim2-undo
[\-\-target\-version N]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B phoenixdkim2-undo
reads a signed message on standard input and walks the
.I Message\-Instance
recipes backward, undoing each modifying hop to reconstruct the message as it
stood at an earlier instance, then writes that message to standard output.  It is
the inverse of the modifying re\-sign path and mirrors the interop
.I dkim2undo
tool.
.PP
The output carries the
.I DKIM2\-Signature
and
.I Message\-Instance
fields whose
.I m=
is at most the target version, the reconstructed content header fields, a blank
line, and the body.  A hop whose recipe is absent or marked irreversible
(a null recipe) cannot be undone and is reported as an error.
.PP
This program is built only when PhoenixDKIM is compiled with experimental DKIM2
support
.RI ( WITH_DKIM2 ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I \-\-target\-version N
The instance to reconstruct back to.  The default
.RI ( -1 )
undoes a single hop (the highest instance minus one);
.I 0
reconstructs the original pre\-signing message (dropping the whole chain).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The message was reconstructed.
.TP
.B 1
A hop could not be undone (missing/irreversible recipe, or nothing to undo).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error, or the message could not be read.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I phoenixdkim2-sign (8),
.I phoenixdkim2-verify (8),
.I phoenixdkim (8)
